  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following regulatory clearance, the operating envelope was extended to include a paediatric sub-population (body surface area < 0.6 m²) operating at reduced flow rates (0.8–1.5 L/min); the original validation campaign covered adult flows of 2.0–6.0 L/min only. The assessment team concluded that the existing validation evidence is representative of the expanded range based on geometric similarity arguments, but no new experimental validation results covering the paediatric flow regime have been generated or linked.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
