      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Observed order of accuracy within 10% of nominal order for the incompressible solver.",
      "rationale": "MMS study (ValidationResult morrison-vr-003) confirmed observed order 1.94, within 3% of nominal second-order scheme. Requirement satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for haemolysis index at the nominal operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study (ValidationResult morrison-vr-002) yielded GCI = 2.1% for NIH at 4.0 L/min adult operating point. Criterion met. The same mesh density is used for paediatric flow simulations; no separate GCI study at paediatric flow rates was performed, but the team judged mesh adequacy to be flow-rate-independent based on the dominant role of impeller geometry in shear stress generation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow, rotational speed, fluid properties) match CFD inputs within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "Adult validation experiments (morrison-vr-001) used phosphate-buffered saline at 37 °C; viscosity and density matched CFD inputs within 1.2%. Flow rates set by calibrated gear pump; rotational speed verified by optical tachometer. All five adult test points within ±3% of nominal CFD boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH within ±15% of measured RH at all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Across the five adult validation points, maximum RH prediction error was 11.4% (at 6.0 L/min, 3500 RPM). Mean absolute error 7.2%. All points within the ±15% acceptance band. No experimental RH measurements exist for the paediatric flow range (0.8–1.5 L/min); the assessment team extrapolated acceptability based on the consistent error trend across the adult range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (RH index) is directly linked to the clinical endpoint and accepted by the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Relative haemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI for both adult and paediatric indications per FDA guidance on pump haemolysis. RH < 1 acceptance criterion is consistent with predicate device comparison methodology. QoI is unchanged by the envelope expansion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities span the operating envelope defined in the COU, or similarity arguments justify extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "The original validation campaign (morrison-vr-001, 2021) covered adult flows 2.0–6.0 L/min, which constituted the entire COU at the time of validation. Following the Q3 2023 paediatric envelope expansion, the lowest validated flow rate (2.0 L/min) exceeds the new paediatric upper bound (1.5 L/min). The assessment team argues that the impeller tip Reynolds number at 1.5 L/min / 2000 RPM overlaps with the lower adult operating points, and that haemolysis mechanisms are dominated by tip-clearance shear rather than bulk flow rate, providing sufficient physical basis to assert coverage without new experimental data. No new validation results at paediatric flows are linked to this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual levels below 1e-5 for all governing equations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to scaled residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; haemolysis scalar transport residual below 1e-7. Convergence monitored via mass-flow imbalance at inlet/outlet (< 0.01%)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition inputs verified against device specifications.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review of simulation setup files completed September 2021. Boundary conditions cross-checked against pump test rig calibration records. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and haemolysis power-law model selection justified by literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal blood pump flows. Giersiepen power-law haemolysis model used with Heuser–Opitz coefficients. Sensitivity analysis across three turbulence models showed RH variation < 8% at adult operating points. Model form uncertainty not re-evaluated for paediatric regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of RH to ±10% variation in key material and geometric inputs quantified.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity study conducted for blood viscosity (±10%), impeller tip clearance (±15 µm), and inlet hematocrit (35–45%). Maximum RH sensitivity 9.3% for tip clearance variation. Inputs bounded by device manufacturing tolerances and clinical operating ranges for adult patients. Paediatric-specific input ranges (e.g., lower hematocrit in neonates) were not separately evaluated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Pump specimens used in validation experiments are geometrically representative of the production device within manufacturing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Three pump specimens used in adult validation experiments; dimensional inspection confirmed all critical dimensions within ±25 µm of nominal CAD geometry used in CFD. Specimens sourced from production batch."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
